volunteer_experiences.description:
During the last week of the summer vacation Stichting Woerdense Vakantieweek organizes a 10-day event during which numerous activities take place for children to participate in: from sports to creative arts and from musicals to funfairs. Over the years the event has grown towards a wider audience, organizing activities for people of the age of 5 to 95. 

The entire event is organized and executed by a group of more than 150 volunteers, from activity planners, light and sound professionals to catering and hands-on support during activities. As part of the HR Committee my main objective is to support volunteers in any I can so that they can perform their activities to the fullest. In this role my responsibilities primarily consist of:

- recruiting new volunteers;
- scheduling the activities of volunteers;
- coaching and supporting volunteers in their daily activities; 
- organizing and leading meetings to prepare volunteers for the new season;
- evaluating the previous event so we can implement best practices in the next event;
- acting as a linking pin between volunteers and the board of the organization.
